The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | BHU student made to strip
                                                                                                               BHU student made to strip
                            
	Lucknow, Sept. 15: A Dalit engineering student was allegedly forced to undress and play a male stripper at Banaras Hindu University, the third ragging case on the campus in two months, reports our special correspondent.        
	Police have taken four second-year students of BHUs information technology wing into custody.         
	University authorities, who lodged the FIR, didnt disclose the identity of the victim, only saying that he was in the first year, came from a state in the south and was a Dalit.        
	The four accused have been suspended for the next four semesters.                                                                                                                                                                            
